@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<style>

    .header-card {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2c3e50, #3498db);
        color: white;
        border-radius: 15px;
        padding: 2rem;
    }

    .section-card {
        background-color: white;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        padding: 20px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

        .section-card h2 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #3498db;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

    .list-custom {
        padding-left: 20px;
    }

        .list-custom li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

    .contact-info {
        background-color: #e9ecef;
        border-left: 4px solid #3498db;
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 5px;
    }

    .footer-text {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
</style>

<!-- Main Content -->
<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="header-card mb-5">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-4"><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead text-center">Welcome to Crypto File! This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our platform for selling files using cryptocurrency. We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring transparency.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> 1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>Our platform allows anonymous registration. You create a unique ID and set a password, which you must store securely. No email address or personally identifiable information is required. We collect only the following data:</p>
        <ul class="list-custom">
            <li><i class="fas fa-user-secret"></i> Your unique ID for account identification.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-link"></i> File links and prices you set for sales pages.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-wallet"></i> Your USDT wallet address for transaction purposes.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>We do not host, store, or access the contents of your files.</strong> You provide external links to files hosted on third-party platforms (e.g., Google Drive, Mega, IPFS). We only store the link URL and price for creating your sales page.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> 2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your data solely to provide and improve our services:</p>
        <ul class="list-custom">
            <li><i class="fas fa-share-alt"></i> To generate and manage your shareable sales pages based on the file links and prices you provide.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-exchange-alt"></i> To process transactions and calculate the 2% fee we retain.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> To transfer the remaining sale amount to your USDT wallet address.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not use your information for marketing or share it with third parties unless required by law.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-money-bill-wave"></i> 3. Transaction and Fees</h2>
        <p>For each sale made through your sales page, Crypto File deducts a 2% fee from the transaction amount. The remaining balance is promptly transferred to your provided USDT wallet address. We do not hold your funds or act as a custodian; all transfers are direct and automated.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> 4. Seller Responsibility</h2>
        <p><strong>You are solely responsible for ensuring that the files you link to are legal, non-infringing, and compliant with all applicable laws.</strong> Crypto File does not review, moderate, or take custody of file content. We act only as a link and payment facilitator.</p>
        <p>In case of reported illegal content, we reserve the right to remove the sales page immediately.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> 5. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your unique ID, wallet address, and transaction data. However, the security of your password and wallet is your responsibility. We recommend using strong, unique passwords and enabling any available security features on your wallet.</p>
        <p>In the event of a data breach, we will notify affected users and take immediate steps to mitigate any harm, to the extent required by applicable law.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-cookie-bite"></i> 6. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>Crypto File does not currently use cookies or tracking technologies. Our platform operates with minimal data collection to ensure your privacy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-handshake"></i> 7. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>We may engage third-party payment processors or blockchain networks to facilitate USDT transactions. These providers have their own privacy policies, and we encourage you to review them. We do not share your unique ID or other data with these parties beyond what is necessary for transactions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-balance-scale"></i> 8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>As a user, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="list-custom">
            <li><i class="fas fa-trash-alt"></i> Request deletion of your unique ID and associated data by contacting us (details below).</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-edit"></i> Update your wallet address at any time through your account settings.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Note that deleting your data will deactivate your sales pages.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-child"></i> 9. Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect data from minors. If we become aware of such data, we will delete it immediately.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-pen"></i> 10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Any updates will be posted here with the revised date. We recommend checking this page periodically for changes. Continued use of the platform after updates constitutes acceptance of the new policy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-card">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> 11. Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="contact-info">If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please reach out to us at:</p>
        <p class="contact-info"><strong>Email:</strong> cryptofile.runasp.net@outlook.com<br><strong>Address:</strong> 12 Emily St, Cambridge, MA 02139, USA</p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center footer-text">
        <p class="text-muted">Last updated: September 28, 2025, 01:29 PM JST</p>
    </div>
</div>
